{"body": "@rafaelfranca the thing I don't like about this currently is you have to wait till you use the association to get the error, and the error doesn't make it obvious what the issue is. If we want to discourage this I would say let's raise an error in the method, but if we did that likely people would ask if we knew what the intent was why not just fix it from the beginning. At the very least we should add some docs to the association methods to say they must use a symbol", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/9352894", "created_at": "2012-10-11T18:44:40Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/7418#issuecomment-9352894", "updated_at": "2012-10-11T18:44:40Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 7418, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/schneems", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/db953d125f5cc49756edb6149f1b813e?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F6ef42a6eab211ddd71ac423a80b42d15.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/received_events", "gravatar_id": "db953d125f5cc49756edb6149f1b813e", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "schneems", "type": "User", "id": 59744, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237fbc9bd3543c15100b87c"}, "id": 9352894, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/7418"}
